4.5 Patch Notes| -Added Windows RDP
Note Update your clients to take advantage of the new feature
|4.4.1 Patch Notes|
-Found an issue in the core networking cuasing stability issues for the past 2 years, it has now been corrected and stability should be finally amazing. (to take advantage please update your clients!) -Reverse Proxy stability completely fixed. -Fixed the notification setting not saving -Fixed random error message popups -Fixed random crashes -Added "Elevate Permissions" feature -Fixed "Dead clients" from the server side
Note #1 Please update your clients! The stability has been improved so much Note #2 Next update look forward to a new feature that's coming out!
|4.4 Patch Notes|
-Improved client/server stability -Recoded Process Watcher system to work on every windows machine -Improved reverse proxy -Improved obfuscation techniques (can now read error messages sent by users) -Fixed visible client mode -Added client watermarking to identify users violating Imminent Monitors terms of service
Note #1: This is a small patch, a much larger update will be out in a few days time
Note #2: Please rebuild your client and update your clients, this update has many network changes, and you won't get all the benifits if you don't update.
|4.3.1 Patch Notes|
-Greatly improved server side stability and performance -Improved remote desktop speed and performance for lower end machines -Ping accuracy fixed -Fixed remote desktop recording bug -Fixed Builder GUI scaling -Fixed plugin tab pages being added as tab headers -Fixed small graphical glitch in File Manager -Fixed small registration issue -Fixed news columns sorting -Fixed settings tab crash -Fixed Command Prompt crash
|4.3 Patch Notes|
This update is a full port to C#, everything has been re-done and general performance should be greatly improved.
More information about this update will be available shortly.
If you have any bug reports please visit https://imminentmethods.net/support
|4.2 Patch Notes|
Note: Please rebuild your client and update your clients, this update has many network changes, and you won't get all the benifits if you don't update.
Additions: -Christmas Theme -Remote Desktop GIF Recording (Beta) -Edge Browser Recovery -Notes for your clients -Client Notification now stacks -Re-Designed Client Notification -"Select Client" added to Client Notification -Added explanations when you hover over options in the Client Builder
Changes: -Client/Server stability improved ALOT -Improved UI Speed
Fixes: -Remote Desktop now works on windows server -Fixed plugin refreshing not refreshing existing loaded plugins -Fixed high memory issue when loading client
|4.1 Patch Notes|
New Features: -Saved Data Viewer (really proud with how this one turned out) -Search Your Clients With IP or Username -OnConnect Commands (include version targeting) -Offline Clients -Added "Install Date" to the main panel
Fixes: -System Wide Injection no Longer Corrupts the Client on 32 Bit Machines -Fixed Remote Desktop Crashing -Fixed Reverse Proxy Crashing -Fixed Possible Random Disconnections
Improvements -Remote Desktop speed and stability improved -Improved Client Connectivity -Improved General Security
|4.0 Update|
Over the past few years Imminent Monitor has been the leading Remote Administration Tool for speed and innovation, it is common for the community to regard Imminent Monitor as a fast Remote Administration Tool with a plethora of features, but stability may be something you have to sacrifice.
I have been working hard to improve the stability issues Imminent Monitor has had in the past and over the past few months it has definitely improved.
Imminent Monitor 4.0 is a brand new revision of Imminent Monitor that focuses on stability, with the same great speeds that you have all grown to love.
I have worked hard on re-coding every aspect of Imminent Monitors core client and have extensively tested each and every feature on multiple operating systems.
Major Changes Below:
-Entire Client Re-Written -Core NetworkHandler has been fully reworked (huge). -Fixed Client crash bug. -Upgraded File Transfer Core, local transfers can now exceed 100 MB/s. -Reverse Proxy 100% stabalized. -Remote Desktop speeds increased, also uses less system resources. -Added Hardware ID Warning. -Client size reduced by 50kb
P.S More changes to be added at a later date.
|3.9.0.11 Patch Notes|
Additions:
-Malware Scanner. -Reads all processes for malicious activity -Detects and removes all major RATs (Luminosity, NanoCore, Babylon, DC, Prototype, LegacyLink, ctOS, Prototype, xRat, PlasmaRAT) -Removes Ring3 Rootkits -Can detect all .net rats even if packed (not native)
Fixes: -Fixed bug where if you disconnect the Client the microphone won't stop trying to send data -Fixed small memory leak
|3.9.0.10 Patch Notes|
Changes/Fixes -Improved General stability of the client (please rebuild to notice changes) -Improved Reverse Proxy stability -Improved Licensing Hardware ID method -Improved Licensing System security -Fixed Licensing System bug where if you register with special characters in your password, you will not be able to log in -Changed news font
Additions -Added Reverse Proxy statistics to the Reverse Proxies Tab (shows each connection a proxy is making plus network statistics)
Please note you must re-compile and update your clients for changes to effect.
|3.9.0.9 Patch Notes|
Additions -Added Opera to Password Recovery -Added FileZilla to Password Recovery -Added new icons for Opera and FileZilla Password Recovery
Changes/Fixes -Chrome Recovery now supports multiple Chrome profiles -Chrome Recovery SQLite Reader fixed -Updated Chrome and Firefox icons to the official icons -Tweaked Dynamic System Wide Injection loop to be more persistent -Fixed two typos in the Clients section "Miscellanous" to "Miscellaneous" and "Text to Speach" to "Text to Speech"
Please note you must re-compile and update your clients for changes to effect.
|3.9.0.8 Patch Notes|
Additions:
-(NEW!) Dynamic System Wide Injection. This feature will watch over (restart if closed) your clients process by injecting native code into random system processes.
-Mouse Cursor added back to Remote Desktop feature.
Fixes:
-Mouse Cursor in Remote Desktop memory leak fixed. -Images in the thumbnail viewer will now show if their extension is upper or lower case. e.g (picture.jpg, picture.JPG)
|3.9.0.7 Patch Notes|
Fixes:
-Reverse Proxy stability improved -When Client disconnects all Reverse Proxies will now be removed -Set Clipboard Text no longer crashes the client -All Auto Updater bugs fixed
Changes:
